Interface DeviceMessageQueue

      • dequeueDeliverableEntry

        DeviceMessageQueue.Entry dequeueDeliverableEntry(java.lang.String path)
        Dequeue message and payload to be delivered. If the entry being dequeued requires acknowledgement, then it is marked as delivered and still kept in the queue until acknowledged; otherwise, it is simply removed from the queue.
        Parameters:
        path - The path of the resource that this message belongs.
        Returns:
        the next entry not delivered or null if none is found.
